# FS-0031 — local e2e env overlay. The REAL `.env.e2e` is gitignored (it carries real secrets).
#
# Create it by copying your working `.env` and overriding ONLY the database URLs to the small,
# disposable e2e DB (so heavy admin pages like /app/blog render locally instead of timing out on the
# full ronindojo_prodsnap). Everything else — BETTER_AUTH_SECRET, BETTER_AUTH_URL,
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_EMAIL, S3_*, STRIPE_*, … — must stay present for t3-env.
# Prisma config also imports `dotenv/config`, and a raw `bunx` child can re-resolve `.env` even when this overlay
# is complete. BOTH URLs remain mandatory, but local Prisma/Playwright work must also use the guarded package
# commands below; the env-file contents alone are not effective-target proof.
#
#   cd apps/web
#   cp .env .env.e2e
#   # then edit .env.e2e so both point at ronindojo_e2e (local user = the one in your .env):
#   #   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://<localuser>@localhost:5432/ronindojo_e2e"
#   #   DIRECT_URL="postgresql://<localuser>@localhost:5432/ronindojo_e2e"
#   bun run e2e:db:setup   # creates + migrates ronindojo_e2e (idempotent; intentionally no seed)
#   # Only if a manual smoke needs reference data such as the BJJ ladder:
#   bun --env-file=.env.e2e prisma/seed.ts
#
# Local run recipe: docs/rituals/closing.md §"E2E run-evidence guard".

DATABASE_URL="postgresql://<localuser>@localhost:5432/ronindojo_e2e"
DIRECT_URL="postgresql://<localuser>@localhost:5432/ronindojo_e2e"
